lock_reason": null, "body": "I tried this code in the rust playground here (https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=05d8e52640801f67b600cef3e03fc6e8)\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nuse std::arch::asm;\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let mut x: u64 = 4;\r\n    let s: u8 = 1;\r\n    unsafe {\r\n        asm!(\r\n            \"mov {tmp}, {x}\",\r\n            \"shl {tmp}, {s}\",\r\n            \"shl {x}, 2\",\r\n            \"add {x}, {tmp}\",\r\n            x = inout(reg) x,\r\n            s = in(reg_byte) s,\r\n            tmp = out(reg) _,\r\n        );\r\n    }\r\n    println!(\"{}\", x);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected to get the output `24`.\r\n\r\nInstead, I got a compiler error as it tried to store `s` in `dl` register.\r\n\r\n```\r\nCompiling playground v0.0.1 (/playground)\r\nerror: invalid operand for instruction\r\n [--> src/main.rs:9:14\r\n](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=05d8e52640801f67b600cef3e03fc6e8#)  |\r\n9 |             \"shl {tmp}, {s}\",\r\n  |              ^\r\n  |\r\nnote: instantiated into assembly here\r\n --> <inline asm>:3:1\r\n  |\r\n3 | shl rcx, dl\r\n  | ^\r\n\r\nerror: could not compile `playground` due to previous error\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe byte code generator for x86 needs to store `s` in `cl` and then it will generate correct code.", "closed_by": {"login": "nagisa", "id": 679122, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY3OTEyMg==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/679122?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/nagisa", "html_url": "https://github.com/nagisa", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nagisa/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nagisa/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nagisa/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nagisa/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nagisa/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/